### Learning Activities & Resources
I spent most of the time going through the learning resources and putting hands-on skill practices by following these tutorials 
- **WordPress Child Themes:** [Child Themes Documentation](https://codex.wordpress.org/Child_Themes) - These offer a Comprehensive guide on creating and using child themes.
- **WPBeginner:** [How to Create a Child Theme in WordPress](https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-create-a-wordpress-child-theme/)
- **YouTube:** [How to Create a Child Theme in WordPress](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8g4n8L1s2G0)

### Content Insights
- Understand the structure of a child theme, including the style.css and functions.php files.
- Learn how to override parent theme styles and functions effectively.

